Friendly staff and great ambiance. Great for breakfast lunch and dinner. Cosy place.

This is a nice place for something to eat, which was perhaps spoilt a little as we had to eat upstairs due to it being small and bust downstairs. I was there last night for the first time. We live around the corner and somehow we always passed by it but never really noticed it until yesterday, when my husband and I were really craving for a good home made soup do to a horrible cold. And we passed bi it, and decided to give it a try. Wow, incredible!!! The lentil soup was delicious, as well as the lobster ravioli and the chicken marsala. We were very please to have discover this restaurant so close to us and so good. The prices are great and the food is excellent and the customer service very friendly at the end of the night the waitress even ask us if we were feeling better by now after the great meal... The food never disappoints. Service can be slow during busy, tourist-packed, weekend brunches. The have an amazing Green Tea Latte which you have to try. They have a wide range of offerings from American comfort food to a decadent Huevos Rancheros, and to Italian bistro bites accompanied by their wines. A neighborhood staple in this part of Harlem.

First visit, the staff was amazing and brunch was delicious. Their latte comes in a large mug and is delicious!! Only down size, this is a small and intimate setting, my friends and I are a party of 10, it would be difficult to have us all there at once as the place seats maybe 20 max. None-the-less, I can't wait for my next visit.

I come here pretty often for breakfast. What I am really feeling at the moment is the granola and yogurt with a side of fruit. I'm pretty full after eating all of that. Its also starting to get more and more popular since its one of the few cafes in harlem that also has a full menu.  The food here is a bit different. For example, instead of just orange juice, they have blood orange juice. Instead of pancakes they have whole wheat blueberry pancakes. If that sounds too fancy for you, you can also get a simple omellete, toast and bacon.  I've tried the whole wheat pancakes and they are a little off, like its missing an ingredient. Also for the cheeseburger, I usually get medium rare and apparently the best they can do is 'medium' although its more like well done.  Despite the few hiccups with the food, still I come here often because of the nice atmosphere and lack of other options in the area.
Nice variety of iced beverages. Had the iced caramel latte, it was delicious!
This is a nice place to enjoy friends and family. Love the songs and decoration.

I heard a lot of great things about this restaurant. So I decided to check it out for brunch. At first it's adorable inside and it has a nice atmosphere.  But that's where it ends. My wife ordered Acapulco Scrambled Eggs, which come with "Fresh Cheese", "Mango", Guacamole...... The Guacamole was dark, which means it was left out and tasted as such. The Fresh cheese tasted a day old, and the eggs were dry. I had the Breakfast Burrito, which had the same old guacamole in it and it wasn't very good. The Cappuccino was terrible and burnt....  Anyways, It was a bummer 'cause I had high hopes for the litte adorable place in Harlem. Did not live up to its rep. boooooooo and Yuuuuuuuuk.
